# {{project_name}}

Accept form submissions, store in D1. Point an HTML form's `action` at `/submit`.

## HTML example

```html
<form action="https://YOUR-WORKER-URL/submit" method="POST">
  <input name="email" type="email" required />
  <input name="name" />
  <textarea name="message"></textarea>
  <button>Submit</button>
</form>
```

Or JSON:
```js
await fetch("https://YOUR-WORKER-URL/submit", {
  method: "POST",
  headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
  body: JSON.stringify({ email: "you@example.com", name: "Ada", message: "hi" }),
});
```

Extra fields (anything beyond email / name / message) land in the `meta` JSON column.

## See submissions

- Quick: open `/submissions` in your browser (delete this endpoint or add auth before going public).
- Proper: open the DB in Cloudflare Studio → D1 → this DB → run `SELECT * FROM submissions ORDER BY created_at DESC;`
